Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @Ginger{1%thumb}. Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @Lime{1}.

== Ginger Rice ==

Melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Jasmine Rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Carrots ==

While rice cooks, toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pickled Scallions and Sweet Soy Mixture ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, juice from half the lime, and a pinch of @salt{}. Set aside to pickle.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon}, remaining ginger, @Wasabi Paste{1%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a squeeze of lime juice. Taste and add more wasabi if you like.

== Chicken ==

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Add sweet soy mixture and simmer until thickened, turning chicken to coat, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

> TIP: If sauce begins to thicken too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper. Toss carrots with @Ponzu Sauce{6%milliliters}.

Divide rice, carrots, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with any remaining sauce from pan and pickled scallion whites (draining first). Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.